# VRM animation playback (Mixamo + studio bar)

## Non-negotiable invariant

When `vrm.humanoid.autoUpdateHumanBones === true` (required for skinning):

1. **AnimationMixer tracks MUST target normalized humanoid bones** (`Normalized_mixamorig*` names from three-vrm), not raw skeleton bones.
2. Each frame after `mixer.update(delta)`: call `humanoid.update()` then `vrm.update(delta)` (`applyVrmHumanoidPose`).
3. Mixer root is `vrm.scene`; loot FBX URLs must stay canonical (`2_Idle.fbx`, not `Idle.fbx`).

Violating (1) causes **silent failure**: mixer time advances, logs show loaded clips, avatar stays frozen.

## Before merging animation changes

Run on Surface (dev server on `:3000`):

```bash
npm run test:anim-regression
npm run test:anim-smoke   # needs https://10.0.0.32:3000
```

Vitest must pass `vrmMixamoPlaybackGuard.test.js` and `loadMixamoAnimation.test.js`.

## Do not revert without replacement

- `resolveVrmBoneTrackName` — normalized before raw
- `setAnimationFrameHook` in sceneManager render/XR loops
- `syncAnimationPrimaryTarget` on VRM load
- Studio bar uses `LOOT_DEFAULT_ANIMATIONS` only (`_studioDefaultsLoaded` blocks trait manifest overwrite)
- `normalizeLootAssetUrl` must not collapse `https://`

## Kimodo (next)

Text/constraint motion from [Kimodo](https://research.nvidia.com/labs/sil/projects/kimodo/) ([HF collection](https://huggingface.co/collections/nvidia/kimodo-v1), [code](https://github.com/nv-tlabs/kimodo)) exports NPZ/AMASS — not Mixamo FBX. Integration path:

- **3DAIGC-API**: Kimodo adapter (SOMA/G1/SMPL-X → studio skeleton)
- **OpenNexus3DStudio**: new clip source alongside loot FBX; reuse `AnimationManager` only after retarget to VRM normalized bones
- Do not bypass `vrmMixamoPlaybackGuard` validation for any new motion format
